## How to run locally.
Docker is the recommended way to run this project locally. Just follow their [instructions](https://docs.docker.com) to get started.

Once everything is configured, just run `docker-compose up` to get the application up and running.

## Database initialization
Run the following command from the terminal `docker-compose run web rake db:migrate`.

## How to run the test suite
Run the following command from the terminal `docker-compose run web rake test`.

## Deployment instructions
Heroku deploys automatically every commit on the `master` branch. So, is very important to keep that branch in a deployable state.